cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.DS, cs.IT, cs.NA

The paper presents a new approach to subspace clustering using linear optimization and spectral clustering. This makes it likely to belong to the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also includes mathematical analysis and complexity analysis, which suggests it could belong to the categories of information theory (cs.IT) and numerical analysis (cs.NA).
